column5: Well... finally got my first part of the action on the Thames this year. My uncle and I went out yesterday.... it was a great day weather wise.... the fishing could have been a little better. Only one fish boated. But it was mine !!! hahah FINALLLLLLLY......  I forgot to mention that its my PB musky too !!!  There was no weight... but she came in at around 47-48 inches. I only got a quick and dirty measure because I had her out of the water for some time ! She was a fat girl as well... I wont estimate the girth, but she was a fatty.... I would say around 20-25# ?   Her back was about 7" across    Well.... I better go get ready.... heading out in about an hour to try and beat it ! hahah  Tight lines !   PS... she swam away good and strong after about 30-40 seconds in the water !!!
Well done, she's a beaut !!
Great job, incredible catch man!  Thanks for sharing, MTBF
very nice!
NICE!!!
Your expression says it all!  Nice fish!
Very nice. What did you catch it on and how deep was the water?Details please.
Now that there's a sweet catch.   Congrats.
nice catch man, looks like a beauty day forsure
Nice Fish!  Did you get a pic for the tournament?
Well done! Got a 44 today to break in my new net!
great looking fish! nicely done and congrats on your pb. From a fellow team 9'er I hope you got another photo...if not go catch a bigger one!
Congratulations Lunker777 on your PB She's a real beauty!!! Thanks for sharing that awesome moment with us! Leechman

Thanks for the comments ! It was a great fish forsure.  I actually didn't get a pic for the tourney because I was worried about gettin her back in the water. Im an idiot I know ! hahah but this weekend I plan on catching a 5/0 so Ill remember to take a pic of that fish !
I love the colour of the fins and tail on it!   Nice fish
Near to hear.... I guess that means it was my falt that we didn't get any (in the boat) when I was out with you?
No, it wasn't your fault. I think it had more to do with your good luck charm; who ever heard of a lucky skunk foot?
hahaha I dont think I would ever let ANYTHING that had to do with a skunk in my boat..... its like your asking to get SKUNKED !!!!  You gunna be out this weekend Brian ?
Awesome Musky!  Congrates on the PB

I was just kidding about the skunk foot. His lucky charm is a banana shaped mirror which he broke while ducking under a ladder to rescue his black cat that ran out in front of an ambulance.  No fishing for me this weekend. I'll be playing the roles of carpenter, accountant, driver, father and husband.
Great fish, on the Thames eh? LOL...guess you dont mean the Thames in London England....lol
Nice ski
Very Nice Ski
